{
  "texts": [
    "In order to evaluate general language abilities, we adopt the Massive Multitask Language Understanding (MMLU) dataset (Hendrycks et al., 2020), a pioneering benchmark designed to evaluate the knowledge acquired during pretraining of language models.",
    "To achieve a fair comparison, we evaluate our models under a 5-shot setting, which keeps the same as our selected baselines.",
    "Evaluation of Music Understanding Abilities.",
    "As introduced in Section 3.3, MusicTheoryBench is a music benchmark proposed in this paper, aiming to inspect the understanding and reasoning capabilities over music knowledge for LLMs.",
    "For the MusicTheoryBench, we report the average accuracy after shuffling the option five times as the final results under a zero-shot setting."
  ]
}